This paper discusses the problem of simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) for autonomous vehicles, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also focuses on the sensor suite design and trade-offs between cost and performance, which involves computer vision (cs.CV), control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
